&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO NAMED INDUSTRY&amp;nbsp;CHAMPION&lt;br /&gt;
IN VALOR 1000 AWARDS FOR THE THIRD TIME&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="margin-left:36.0pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, September 6, 2022 -&lt;/strong&gt; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho won the Bioenergy category in the 2022 edition of the Valor 1000 Awards sponsored by the newspaper &lt;em&gt;Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico&lt;/em&gt; in partnership with the Get&amp;uacute;lio Vargas Foundation (FGV) and Serasa Experian. The awards ranks Brazil&amp;rsquo;s one thousand largest companies based on the best results and performance in 27 economic sectors (26 companies and 1 financial institution).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the awards ceremony hosted at Hotel Unique in S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, on September 5, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho was represented by its Chief Financial and Investor Relations Officer, Felipe Vicchiato.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Company was elected sector champion in the Valor 1000 for the third time. In 2017 and 2020, it won in the Sugar &amp;amp; Ethanol category (which in the 2022 edition was renamed Bioenergy), and in the latter edition also was named Valor Company (champion of sector champions).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition to Felipe Vicchiato, the awards ceremony was attended by Maur&amp;iacute;cio Krug Ometto, Chairman of the Board of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho; Marcelo Campos Ometto, Council Member; Luciana Carvas, Human Resources, Health and Safety Officer; and Helder Gosling, Commercial and Logistics Officer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Valor 1000&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Valor 1000 is the largest and most important yearbook of Brazilian companies. The publication brings exclusive indicators and a ranking of the 1,000 largest companies in the company by net revenue.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Valor 1000 winners are based on the performance of the companies compiled in the ranking in accounting and financial criteria. For the ranking&amp;rsquo;s 22&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; edition, 1,069 non-financial companies were analyzed by Valor and its partners Serasa Experian and the Center for Financial Studies of the S&amp;atilde;o Paulo Business School of the Get&amp;uacute;lio Vargas Foundation (FGV/CEF/EASP/FGVSP).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This year&amp;rsquo;s edition also featured a change in the process for evaluating sector champions, with the three highest-ranking companies in the six financial accounting criteria moving on to the second phase, where they are evaluated by a committee of eight market specialists in Environment, Social and Governance (ESG) practices. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=G2wzCOkS4UQhv7W0XORN1Q==" style="width: 150px; height: 244px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=Ysq9fhAQhBksteI2OVyLZA==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Wed, 27 Jul 2022 09:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho: one of Brazil’s most innovative companies</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;ONE OF BRAZIL&amp;rsquo;S MOST INNOVATIVE COMPANIES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, July 27, 2022&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; A S&amp;atilde;o Martinho is among the 150 most innovative companies in Brazil for the seventh time in a row. The 8&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of &amp;ldquo;Valor Inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Brasil Award&amp;rdquo;, organized by Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico newspaper in partnership with consulting firm Strategy&amp;amp; and ANPEI, disclosed its annual ranking at an online ceremony &amp;ndash; the Company ranked 61&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; in the national ranking.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In the agribusiness sector, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho remained in a prominent position, ranking 4&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; among the five best and most innovative companies. This is the 6&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the award since 2016 in which the Company ensures its place among the industry&amp;rsquo;s Top 5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;With the topic &amp;ldquo;5G and the revolution in business models,&amp;rdquo; this year&amp;rsquo;s survey revealed the companies with the best innovation management and their investments in the local market. Based on qualitative and quantitative indicators, five pillars in the innovation chain were assessed: intention to innovate, effort to make the innovation happen, results obtained, market assessment and knowledge generation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;We believe that innovation creates sustainable value for our Company. In the past years, we have been following our digital transformation journey, turning S&amp;atilde;o Martinho into one of the biggest smart farming cases in Brazil, making the first tests with the 5G network in the agribusiness sector. We seek to develop business and solutions, fostering open innovation and increasingly connecting our Company to the best players in the ecosystem,&amp;rdquo; states Agenor Pavan, COO and vice-president of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;For more information on the 8&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of &amp;ldquo;Valor Inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Brasil Award&amp;rdquo;, visit:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.premioinovacao2022.com.br/"&gt;premioinovacao2022.com.br&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=E4yPN+SgHVDDCe7/XmqdzA==" style="width: 350px; height: 183px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=d+ibau4bCwCb1COjUxQOaQ==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Thu, 30 Jun 2022 19:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho among the 10 best companies in the Broadcast Empresas ranking</title><description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO AMONG THE 10 BEST COMPANIES&lt;br /&gt;
IN THE BROADCAST EMPRESAS RANKING&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Company stood out for its financial performance and return to shareholders in 2021&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, June 30, 2022 &lt;/strong&gt;- S&amp;atilde;o Martinho was one of the 10 Brazilian companies honored in the 22nd edition of &amp;ldquo;Pr&amp;ecirc;mio Broadcast Empresas&amp;rdquo; [Broadcast Companies Award], held by Ag&amp;ecirc;ncia Estado in partnership with FGV.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The annual ranking presented the 10 companies listed on B3 with the best financial performance and return to shareholders in 2021, which stood out in various criteria and indicators, such as variation in equity profitability; payment of dividends in relation to equity; price/earnings ratio (PE); price-to-book value (P/BV); stock fluctuation; stock volatility; and liquidity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In addition to S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, the following companies were also awarded: WEG, RaiaDrogasil, Klabin, JBS, Braskem, Vale, Rede d&amp;#39;Or, Ambev, and Arezzo, among 204 companies assessed in the market.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;According to Fabio Venturelli, CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, being among the 10 outstanding companies is a great honor for the Company and a very important recognition of the care taken with the management of the business. &amp;ldquo;I share this recognition with the entire company, and our more than 12,000 employees, who together make a difference,&amp;rdquo; he said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=OeJF2UMxyTpsx71NhjgBgA==" style="width: 300px; height: 220px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=8L0BkTvwfVOwctCrZwNdAQ==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jun 2022 19:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho reports cash net income of R$ 219.0 million in 4Q22, down 4.2%</title><description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO REPORTS CASH NET INCOME OF R$ 219.0 MILLION&lt;br /&gt;
IN 4Q22, DOWN 4.2%&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Company announces to the market its financial results&lt;br /&gt;
for the 4&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; quarter of 2021/22 crop year&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, June 20, 2022 -&lt;/strong&gt; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has announced the results of the fourth quarter and the overall results of the 2021/22 crop year. Agricultural yield and TRS produced decreased significantly during the crop year. In this context, the company adjusted its production mix, which enabled it to achieve healthy results. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In 4Q22, Adjusted EBITDA totaled R$ 770.8 million, increasing 35.6%, with Adjusted EBITDA margin of 51.9%. In the crop year, Adjusted EBITDA totaled R$ 3,141.9 million (+43.6%), with margin of 54.5%, mainly reflecting the higher average selling prices of ethanol and sugar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Net Income in 4Q22 was R$ 225.4 million, increasing 8.7% from 4Q21. In 12M22, net income totaled R$ 1,480.9 million, up 59.7%. Cash net income totaled R$ 219.0 million in the quarter, down 4.2% from 4Q21, while cash net income in the crop year totaled R$ 1,528.6 million, increasing 53.4% from the previous year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Another important financial indicator for the Company - the Leverage Ratio - ended the crop year at 0.93x Net Debt/Adjusted EBITDA on March 31, 2022, down 25.1% from March 31, 2021.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=YGKYNHuO9STMPnwq2hEo6A==" style="width: 300px; height: 200px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho Mill&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=6UZHW+4GrZOjGjP2stw5cA==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Mon, 04 Apr 2022 15:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho raises R$ 1.098 billion through incentivized debentures for green projects</title><description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO RAISES R$ 1.098 BILLION THROUGH INCENTIVIZED DEBENTURES&lt;br /&gt;
FOR GREEN PROJECTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, April&amp;nbsp;4, 2022 - &lt;/strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, one of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s largest sugar and ethanol groups, has recently announced that it raised R$1.098 billion through a public offering of incentivized debentures to finance investments in the production and storage of biofuels and biomass in its units.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The issue received the Green Seal from S&amp;amp;P Global Ratings and certifies its alignment with the Green Bond Principles (GBP) of the International Capital Market Association (ICMA), which underscores the transparent use of funds and the focus on sustainable actions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;XP was the sole lead manager of the debenture offering.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=dWImhs00DnhmZM/MN3ghPw==" style="width: 300px; height: 200px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sugar-cane at S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=GrijPNzRgNuU2tOvnEZfsQ==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Mon, 14 Feb 2022 22:55:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho reports net income of R$ 696.9 million in 3Q22, up 156.1%</title><description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REPORTS NET INCOME OF R$ &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;696.9 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MILLION IN 3Q22, UP &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;156.1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;%&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Company announces to the market its financial results for the 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; quarter&lt;br /&gt;
of the 2021/22 crop year&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, February 14, 2022 - &lt;/strong&gt;At the end of one more quarter of the 2021/22 crop year, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has reported healthy performance in its key financial indicators, with the highlight being net income of R$696.9 million in 3Q22, increasing 156.1% from the same period the previous crop year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Net revenue in the period was around R$ 1.53 billion, up 26.2% from 3Q21. Fueled by better average sale prices of ethanol (+76.9%) and sugar (+30.9%) in the market, adjusted EBITDA totaled R$892.8 million, 37% higher than in the previous year. EBITDA margin stood at 58.3% in 3Q22.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;From the operational viewpoint, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has already concluded its crushing period for the 2021/22 crop year, processing 19.9 million tons of sugarcane in 9M22, 11.6% less than in the same period the previous crop year, mainly due to the prolonged drought in the period and fewer harvest days than in 9M21.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;During the current crop year, the company produced around 1.3 million tons of sugar, down 12.1% from the 2020/21 crop year, as well as 913,000 m&amp;sup3; of ethanol (-10.4%) and 760,000 MWh of energy exported (-8.9%). The sugar/ethanol production mix remained stable year on year at 47%-53%. The TRS produced in the first nine months of the crop year was 11% lower than in the same period the previous crop year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Finally, the company&amp;#39;s leverage ratio (Net Debt/Adjusted EBITDA) at the end of 3Q21 was 1.15x, about 10% lower than on December 31, 2020.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=YGKYNHuO9STMPnwq2hEo6A==" style="width: 300px; height: 200px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho Mill&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=wkjP7apOe7fTnQta1pobeQ==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Thu, 27 Jan 2022 15:32:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Iracema Mill receives ISO 14001 certification</title><description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;IRACEMA MILL RECEIVES ISO 14001 CERTIFICATION&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Mill is certified after implementing an Environmental Management System in its agroindustrial and administrative areas and conducting an independent audit&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, January 27, 2022 &lt;/strong&gt;- The Iracema Mill, located in Iracem&amp;aacute;polis, S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, was certified by ISO 14001, an international standard that set the criteria for implementing an Environmental Management System (EMS) devised for the unit,&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;which established various operational practices, especially to ensure compliance with environmental legislation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Drawing on the involvement of employees from all areas of the company (agricultural, industrial and administrative), the unit underwent a lengthy diagnosis and audit process, from October 2020 to October 2021, which evaluated compliance with the standard&amp;rsquo;s requirements. These include, for example, creating management systematics for environmental impacts; controlling and assessing compliance with environmental legislation; mapping risks; optimizing processes for responsibly using, protecting and avoiding natural resources, among others.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Training programs were also organized to ensure that employees were even better prepared to perform their functions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;After conducting the diagnosis, implementing the EMS and completing the certification audit, which was performed by the Carlos Alberto Vanzolini Foundation (FCAV), the unit obtained the certification, which attests to the proper environmental management of its operations and production processes, as well as its commitment to the environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Attaining ISO 14001 demonstrates S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;rsquo;s respect for the environment, environmental legislation and the requirements of international standards. Requiring continuous improvement, the certification will ensure that the company continues to meet the market&amp;rsquo;s ever-higher expectations in terms of responsible care and corporate governance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Today, in addition to the Iracema Mill, the Santa Cruz Mill also holds ISO 14001 certification. The company expects to expand soon its implementation of EMSs in accordance with the 14001 standard to its other units, the S&amp;atilde;o Martinho and Boa Vista mills.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=aCBU3cksBEeCVIvN+Q9BxQ==" style="width: 250px; height: 188px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=FWySdeFlqHcs1JEyQnfRng==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Wed, 22 Dec 2021 20:23:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho wins Valor Career Award for second straight year</title><description>&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO WINS VALOR CAREER AWARD FOR BEST COMPANY IN PEOPLE MANAGEMENT FOR SECOND STRAIGHT YEAR&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, December 22, 2021 &lt;/b&gt;&amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has won a Valor Career Award for the second straight year, being named Best Company in People Management in the category of &amp;ldquo;7,001 to 17,000 employees.&amp;rdquo; The 19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the awards, which are sponsored by the newspaper &lt;i&gt;Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico&lt;/i&gt; in partnership with the consulting firm Mercer, announced the winners in an online ceremony on December 22, in which various HR leaders from Brazil&amp;rsquo;s most important companies participated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Based on Mercer&amp;rsquo;s global Prosperity &amp;amp; Engagement methodology, the awards identify and recognize companies that reinvent themselves, are ahead of their time and have distinguished themselves for offering a workplace in which the employee experience figures a key mechanism for managing their businesses prosperously and sustainably.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Held annually, the Valor Career Awards highlight Brazil&amp;rsquo;s best companies in people management based on the opinions of their employees. Employees and professionals in the human resources department of each participating company complete a confidential survey that measures the level of engagement and prosperity of the organizations&amp;rsquo; workers. In all, the five best companies were recognized in 35 categories based on the number of employees, as well as the grand champion of the 19&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the awards.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Valor Career Awards are open to companies in any industry with over 100 employees and at least two years of operations in Brazil. In 2021, 117 companies were assessed based on surveys submitted by 56,000 respondents. Over the survey&amp;rsquo;s last three editions, 377 companies have been involved and on average 53,000 employees participated each year by completing the survey&amp;rsquo;s questionnaires.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;According to Luciana Carvas, Chief Human Resources Officer at S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, winning such an important award for the second straight year clearly shows that the company is advancing on its journey of continuous improvement and constantly strengthening and evolving its organizational culture guided by the key value of caring for people.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;It is with great pride and gratitude that our Human Resources team, our executive team and all our employees once again are honored by this recognition from Valor Career. S&amp;atilde;o Martinho successfully navigated yet another challenging year in which it delivered results that were only made possible thanks to our highly qualified and engaged workers who constantly strive for excellence in a workplace that stimulates human and professional development,&amp;rdquo; she concluded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=LePvwzMkQ6onCcKgbyBm0Q==" style="width: 200px; height: 280px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=LIWTNB+1hEM6qLix3ceZtw==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Mon, 06 Dec 2021 18:22:00 GMT</pubDate><title>New Sesi school pays tribute to member of Ometto family in Ribeirão Preto</title><description>&lt;p align="center" style="margin-left:6.75pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center" style="margin-left:6.75pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NEW SESI SCHOOL PAYS TRIBUTE TO MEMBER OF OMETTO FAMILY&lt;br /&gt;
IN RIBEIR&amp;Atilde;O PRETO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center" style="margin-left:6.75pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto, December 6, 2021&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; SESI-SP&amp;rsquo;s new educational unit was officially opened in Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto (SP), on December 4, under the name Escola Sesi &amp;quot;Dr. Orlando Ometto.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The institution pays tribute to doctor Orlando Ometto, who was a former CEO of Usina S&amp;atilde;o Martinho and former mayor of Prad&amp;oacute;polis (SP) for two terms of office, between 1969 and 1982, and made a significant contribution to the development of the region. The event was attended by Paulo Skaf, president of Fiesp and Sesi-SP, representatives of the Ometto family, the mayor of Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto, Mr. Duarte Nogueira, employees of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, and other local authorities.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Operating since July 2019 in the district of Planalto Verde, the new school features 25 classrooms, Science and Technology, Physical Science, Chemistry and Biology laboratories, in addition to a modern Media and Technology laboratory. The structure also offers a sports court, a kitchen and two cafeterias. The unit currently serves 1,000 Elementary and High School students.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=1ZjQXrf56p6dsewBECKnRw==" style="width: 350px; height: 233px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

