&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Company announces to the market its financial results&lt;br /&gt;
for the 2&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; quarter of the 2021/22 crop year&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, November 8, 2021&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has once again reported positive financial results in the second quarter of the current 2021/22 crop year. &amp;nbsp;Highlights include net income of R$368.4 million, an increase of 11% from the same period last crop year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In 2Q22, net revenue totaled R$1,425.7 million, 54% higher than in 2Q21, mainly reflecting the better sales prices for sugar (+43%), ethanol (+68.2%) and energy (+47.9%) during the quarter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;This effect also drove the growth of adjusted EBITDA in the quarter, which totaled R$790 million, 65.9% higher than in 2Q21, with EBITDA margin of 55.4% (+4.0 p.p.).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;On the operations front, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho announced the conclusion of the crushing period for the 2021/22 crop year, during which it processed 19.8 million tons of sugarcane, 11.7% less than in the same period last crop year, mainly due to climatic factors such as prolonged drought and frost in July, in addition to fewer harvest days. Total Recoverable Sugar (TRS) produced in the crop year stood at 2,916,000 tons, down 11.1% from the same period last crop year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;With regard to its flagship products, the company produced approximately 1.3 million tons of sugar, 12.1% less than in the 2020/21 crop year, 910 thousand m&amp;sup3; of ethanol, including 389 thousand m&amp;sup3; of anhydrous ethanol (+13.5 %) and 521 thousand m&amp;sup3; of hydrous ethanol (-22.8%), and 750 thousand MWh of exported energy (-14.7%). The sugar/ethanol production mix remained stable in the annual comparison, at 47%/53%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Another important financial indicator for S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, the leverage ratio (net debt/adjusted EBITDA), stood at 1.21x on September 30, 2021, 12.5% lower than on the same date in 2020.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=B+xWSCsAYOyuC9UQNmLhFg==" style="width: 350px; height: 233px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho Mill&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=EoKKM5bhPqMvzMn2nWwPVw==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Thu, 28 Oct 2021 15:34:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho is elected one of the most innovative companies in Brazil</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO IS ELECTED ONE OF THE&lt;br /&gt;
MOST INNOVATIVE COMPANIES IN BRAZIL&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, October 28, 2021&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho is once again among the 150 most innovative companies in the country. At the 7&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the &amp;ldquo;Pr&amp;ecirc;mio Valor Inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Brasil&amp;rdquo; organized by the Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico newspaper in partnership with Strategy&amp;amp;, a consulting firm, and the National Research and Development Association of Innovative Companies (ANPEI), the company reached its best position ever (54&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;) in the nationwide ranking, climbing 33 positions in relation to 2020. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In the sectoral ranking, the company remained among the five best and most innovative in Agribusiness, coming in at 4&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;. This is the fifth edition of the awards - 2016, 2018, 2019, 2020 and 2021 - in which S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has ranked among the industry Top 5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;At an online ceremony held on October 27, awards were given in recognition of management models, investment capacity and results achieved through innovation at the biggest companies in Brazil across 23 sectors of the economy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The ranking was compiled using quantitative and qualitative indicators based on five pillars of the innovation chain: intention to innovate, innovation efforts, results obtained, market assessment and generation of knowledge. The survey also sought to assess and understand how companies are preparing themselves today to develop innovations in data security and cybernetics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;According to Agenor Pavan, COO and vice president of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, the award once again proves the company&amp;#39;s capacity to transform knowledge into new solutions for the agribusiness sector, backed by the dedication of all its employees, in the pursuit of new products and business opportunities. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;For the near future, new investment structures are being considered in our strategic plans to further drive innovation across the company,&amp;rdquo; he said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;For further information about the 7&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of &amp;ldquo;Pr&amp;ecirc;mio Valor Inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Brasil&amp;rdquo;, visit &lt;a href="https://premioinovacaobrasil2021.com.br/"&gt;premioinovacaobrasil2021.com.br&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=cHIkoTyjTGAD3q+iGGkcwA==" style="width: 400px; height: 209px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=3I9egasSHOPANhYvacJFSg==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Mon, 25 Oct 2021 17:52:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Fabio Venturelli elected one of 10 best CEOs in Brazil</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;FABIO VENTURELLI ELECTED ONE OF 10 BEST CEOS IN BRAZIL&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, October 25, 2021&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Fabio Venturelli, CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, has been elected one of the &amp;quot;10 best CEOs in Brazil&amp;quot; in 2021 by Forbes magazine.&amp;nbsp; According to Forbes in its September edition, the executives chosen were who &amp;quot;best faced the health and economic crisis scenario, while maintaining or even improving the significance of their brands and the financial indicators of their businesses.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In the brief profile featured in the magazine, Fabio describes the main challenges faced by the company&amp;#39;s management during the pandemic, the strategies used to keep field operations safe and the opportunities he discovered to accelerate business. &amp;quot;In the face of the greatest adversity, we delivered the best results in history (...) I always envisioned - and we built - a company that was resilient to the point of generating results even during the worst moments,&amp;quot; he recalls. He also reveals some of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;#39;s plans for the future: going digital and driving innovation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The Forbes list of best CEOs was compiled in partnership with professors at FGV, capital market professionals and entities, as well as boards of directors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;500 Latin America&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In October, Venturelli was also selected to &amp;ldquo;&lt;a href="https://www.bloomberglinea.com.br/especiales/500-pessoas-mais-influentes-america-latina/"&gt;500 Latin America&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rdquo;, a list published by the news platform Bloomberg L&amp;iacute;nea of the 500 most influential people in the Latam region across diverse sectors and activities, including entrepreneurs, philanthropists, athletes and public authorities from 18 countries. According to the platform, the list is not a ranking but a selection of personalities who are &amp;ldquo;inspiring and resilient&amp;rdquo; leaders capable of generating value in their sectors, especially during the pandemic. &amp;ldquo;The selection focused on the efforts taken by many of these individuals to contain and address the effects of the COVID-19 pandemic.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=VbnRIbgJ8IFqCvf2F4l+GA==" style="width: 250px; height: 329px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fabio Venturelli on the cover of Forbes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
