&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO REPORTS CASH INCOME OF R$996.5 MILLION IN 2020/21 CROP YEAR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;The Company disclosed the financial results of the 4&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; quarter of the 2020/21 crop year, ending another year with positive performance&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, June 21, 2021&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;-&lt;/strong&gt; Thanks to the dedication and commitment of over 12,000 employees, the Company conducted its operations safely throughout the crop year amidst the pandemic to conclude a year of financial and operational records.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The Company registered Cash Income of R$996.5 million, 39.7% higher than in the 12 previous months, and R$228.7 million in 4Q21 (+38.7%). Net Income totaled R$927.1 million in 12M21 (+45.1%) and R$207.4 million in 4Q21 (+45.4%). Adjusted EBITDA was R$2,188 million in 12M21 (+17.8%) and R$568.2 million in 4Q21 (-1.9%).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Sugarcane processed at the Company&amp;#39;s four mills totaled 22.5 million tons during the 2020/21 crop year, down 0.5% from the volume processed in the previous year, due to drier weather in the main production regions. &amp;nbsp;However, this scenario resulted in total TRS production of 3,282 thousand tons during the period (+4.0%).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Among its flagship products, the Company produced around 1,483 thousand tons of sugar and 1,018 thousand m&amp;sup3; of ethanol, an increase of 34.1% and decrease of 13.1%, respectively, in relation to the previous crop year. As such, the sugar-ethanol production mix stood at 47% &amp;ndash; 53%. The increase in sugar production during the 2020/21 crop year compared to the previous year was mainly due to higher sugar prices and profitability compared to ethanol.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Still on financial indicators, the Company&amp;#39;s Financial Leverage, as measured by the ratio of Net Debt to Adjusted EBITDA, continued the downward trend of previous quarters to reach 1.24x on March 31, 2021, declining 20.3% from March 31, 2020.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Vision of the Future&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The Company&amp;rsquo;s performance during the crop year was accompanied by other achievements and market recognition. The Company retained its Investment Grade rating assigned by Standard &amp;amp; Poor&amp;#39;s, an important attestation to its financial management, debt levels and results. Moreover, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho was included in the new S&amp;amp;P/B3 Brasil ESG Index of B3, underlining its commitment to business sustainability. The Company&amp;#39;s market capitalization at B3 was R$10.5 billion on March 31, 2021, and surpassed R$13 billion in June.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Based on its vision of the future, with the focus on business sustainability and innovation, after approval by the Board of Directors, the Company announced in early 2021 the construction of a new plant to produce ethanol from corn processing, adjacent to the Boa Vista Mill (UBV) in the state of Goi&amp;aacute;s. This new plant will use residual bagasse (biomass) from the UBV to generate power for the operation, thus resulting in a cleaner and more sustainable process.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The agriculture 4.0 project, aimed at an increasingly agile and efficient agro-industrial management, continues to advance across all units of the Company and should generate important operational gains over the coming years. &amp;nbsp;In this regard, the Company had announced in 2020 a partnership with Ericsson and is already testing the 5G technology at the S&amp;atilde;o Martinho Mill.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

