&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO LAUNCHES DIGITAL SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY PLATFORM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;The new platform presents the Company&amp;rsquo;s private social investment criteria for meeting requests for donations, social projects and sponsorships&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, March 22, 2021 -&lt;/strong&gt; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, one of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s largest sugar and ethanol groups, has launched its new digital Social Responsibility platform for meeting requests for donations, social projects and sponsorships from civil society to benefit communities near its four mills, which are located in Prad&amp;oacute;polis, Iracem&amp;aacute;polis and Am&amp;eacute;rico Brasiliense in the countryside region of S&amp;atilde;o Paulo and in Quirin&amp;oacute;polis in the state of Goi&amp;aacute;s.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The Private Social Investment (PSI) platform is already operating on S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;rsquo;s website&amp;nbsp; (&lt;a href="http://www.isp.saomartinho.com.br"&gt;isp.saomartinho.com.br&lt;/a&gt;) with comprehensive information on guidelines for the voluntary allocation of the Company&amp;rsquo;s financial, human and material resources to support social projects focusing on actions to promote education for all ages and support the environment and diversity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;On the platform, visitors can see all the projects already supported by the Company, the employee volunteer campaigns and the latest news in social responsibility at S&amp;atilde;o Martinho.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;For those interested in obtaining the Company&amp;rsquo;s support, the PSI platform allows them to easily and quickly submit a proposal and present their social project using an online form. All requests are analyzed directly by the Social Responsibility team based on S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;rsquo;s criteria and its new PSI guidelines, and responses are sent within a period of 60 days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;The new platform represents a major advance in our social responsibility activities by facilitating more open and dynamic relationships with civil society and local communities. We want to invest more in basic and professional education, culture, the environment and sports, always working in partnership with various social institutions, striving for transparency in our actions and respect for people and local cultures. With this initiative, we hope to engage and impact more projects with the potential to support social development so that together we can offer new opportunities and build a better future,&amp;rdquo; said Luciana Carvas, HR and Social Responsibility director at S&amp;atilde;o Martinho.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Learn more: &lt;a href="https://isp.saomartinho.com.br"&gt;isp.saomartinho.com.br&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

