&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO WINS VALOR CAREER AWARD&lt;br /&gt;
FOR BEST COMPANY IN PEOPLE MANAGEMENT&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, November 30, 2020&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has won the Valor Career 2020 Award for Best Company in People Management in the category of &amp;ldquo;7,001 to 17,000 employees.&amp;rdquo; The 18&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the awards, which are sponsored by the newspaper &lt;em&gt;Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico&lt;/em&gt; in partnership with the consulting firm Mercer, announced the winners in an online ceremony on November 30, in which various HR leaders from Brazil&amp;rsquo;s most important companies participated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The annual awards feature Brazil&amp;rsquo;s best companies in people management based on the opinions of employees. For this, the employees and professionals of the human resources department of each company completed a confidential survey that measures the level of engagement and progress of employees inside the organizations. The five best companies are selected in each of the categories, which are based on the number of employees.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In an exceptional year because of the covid-19 pandemic, this edition of the awards also evaluated how companies addressed their employees&amp;rsquo; experience during the need for physical distancing, given the changes in work routines and the new precautions involving health and social relations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;According to Luciana Carvas, Chief Human Resources Officer at S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, the award is a recognition of the company&amp;rsquo;s strong and consolidated organizational culture in which caring for people is key to the success of the business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho works to give its employees a workplace focused on human and professional development, accompanied by opportunities for technical training and big challenges. In a challenging year like 2020, our employees made all difference, which led us to achieve excellent results, always in a safe workplace and with the drive to collaborate. This award fills us with pride and leaves us confident on the path we are following. I take this opportunity to thank the Human Resources team, the executive team and all our employees,&amp;rdquo; she said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=BBv2XhynYiXzV4bZVC8hiA==" style="width: 160px; height: 225px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=t7Wh3bFlrHLh6Xn4NVjGWQ==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Thu, 29 Oct 2020 17:22:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho named Company of the Year and Sugar and Ethanol champion in Valor 1000 Awards</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO NAMED COMPANY OF THE YEAR&lt;br /&gt;
AND SUGAR AND ETHANOL CHAMPION IN VALOR 1000 AWARDS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="margin-left:36.0pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, October 29&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;, 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho garnered prominent position in the 2020 edition of the Valor 1000 Awards, which are sponsored by the newspaper Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico in partnership with the Get&amp;uacute;lio Vargas Foundation and Serasa Experian. The awards compile the country&amp;rsquo;s one thousand largest companies with the best results and performance in 25 industries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;At the online ceremony, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho was named the Company of Year 2020 as well as champion of the Sugar &amp;amp; Ethanol industry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;In a year of unprecedented challenges for everyone, this recognition demonstrates our company&amp;rsquo;s capacity to surpass expectations and our potential to increase and improve our deliveries, while creating value for the agribusiness sector as a whole in Brazil,&amp;rdquo; said Fabio Venturelli, CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho S.A.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In its 20&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition, the Valor 1000 Yearbook compiles a ranking of the one thousand largest companies in Brazil, which combined reported sales of over R$4.3 trillion in 2019.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Valor 1000 evaluates companies in 25 sectors using net revenue as the parameter for this inclusion in the ranking and adopts various criteria for measuring performance, such as EBITDA and liability management. The yearbook offers analyses of the companies&amp;rsquo; results, highlights industry and macroeconomic conditions that influence the market and presents the companies&amp;rsquo; expectations for the post-pandemic period.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;To compile the ranking and select the champions for this year, the Center for Finance Studies (FGVcef) of the S&amp;atilde;o Paulo Business School (EAESP) of FGV and Serasa Experian conducted analyses of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s largest companies based on survey questionnaires and on their financial statements reported to the market.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho highlighted over 2020&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Over the year, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has garnered various accolades. In addition to being named Valor Company 2020 and Best Company in the Sugar &amp;amp; Ethanol sector by the Valor 1000 Yearbook, it also was highlighted in various surveys and awards conducted by the newspaper Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In September, for the fifth straight year, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho was named one of the 150 most innovative companies in the country in the sixth edition of the Valor Innovation Brazil Awards 2020, which was based on a survey compiled by the newspaper in partnership with Strategy&amp;amp;, a strategic consulting firm of PwC. In four recent editions of the awards (2016, 2018, 2019 and 2020), S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has figured among the top five companies in the ranking of the agribusiness sector.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In August, the Valor Executive Awards named, for the sixth time, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho CEO Fabio Venturelli as Executive of the Year in the Agribusiness category. Fabio Venturelli already had received the honor from Valor in 2012, 2013, 2016, 2017 and 2018.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=yIparlEeQDUHB/+k9y/R1Q==" style="width: 150px; height: 244px;" /&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=Hd7ciRlOyfloNswMVu1/Bg==" style="width: 150px; height: 244px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=eQ60Gy5nAZXZn0VCanH0YA==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Wed, 30 Sep 2020 19:03:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho and Ericsson establish strategic partnership for the development of 5G solutions for Agribusiness</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO AND ERICSSON ESTABLISH STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIP FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF 5G SOLUTIONS FOR AGRIBUSINESS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align="center"&gt;Agreement includes the development of joint actions in research and innovation, with focus on increasing agricultural and industrial efficiency, leveraging the recent investments in agricultural connectivity - &amp;ldquo;PROJECT COA&amp;rdquo; - developed by S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="margin-left:36.0pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, September 30&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;, 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho SA (SMTO3), a world reference in agroindustrial management, which is among the largest sugar-energy groups in Brazil, and Ericsson (NASDAQ: ERIC), leader in the telecommunications sector, announce an unprecedented agreement in the country, focused on the development of technological innovations for agribusiness to be applied in the IoT (Internet of Things) environment, based on open standards of 4G and 5G connectivity. This initiative will increase the speed of transformation of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;#39;s farms into &lt;em&gt;Smart Farming&lt;/em&gt; through 5G connectivity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho chose Ericsson as a partner to enable 5G coverage of the entire operation of the S&amp;atilde;o Martinho Plant, considered the largest sugarcane processing unit in the world, located in the city of Prad&amp;oacute;polis, where an innovation center will be installed to develop real 5G applications for agribusiness, using 700MHz and 3500MHz frequencies. As next step, a telecom operator, still to be defined, will selected by S&amp;atilde;o Martinho to be part of the partnership.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;To complete the ecosystem, the participation of entrepreneurs and startups are also expected, enabling more agile and flexible integrations between companies and agribusiness developers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The use cases of 5G technology, generated as a result of this partnership, will increase S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;rsquo;s efficiency in processes that require high speed of data transfer and a very low latency (response time), allowing the use of autonomous vehicles such as tractors and trucks, drones for intelligent control of pests and weeds, identification and location of fires in their agricultural areas, among other activities that require data processing and high-speed image.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;The agribusiness sector corresponds to almost 25% of the Brazilian GDP, and only 29% of rural properties are connected, which represents a restrictive factor for innovation and productivity. This is a sector that deserves even more attention when it comes to reducing the digital spread. Currently Brazil occupies the third position in the Agribusiness Export Ranking in the world. Thus, any benefit generated by this partnership between Ericsson and S&amp;atilde;o Martinho will have a strong positive impact and will support the growth of the Brazilian economy&amp;rdquo;, says Eduardo Ricotta, Ericsson CEO of Latam South, reinforcing the commitment that company assumed to support S&amp;atilde;o Martinho in the digital transformation of its farms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A sectoral analysis developed by Ericsson showed that connectivity in the countryside will bring a similar disruption to that brought in the 1960s with the tractor, with significant benefits in all aspects of agriculture. The digitalization potential of the Brazilian economy, combined with the maturity of information technologies and communication sector and the consequent emergence of a digital ecosystem, now creates a favorable environment for digital transformation in the countryside, enabled by connectivity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;We are very happy to be able to support S&amp;atilde;o Martinho in this important step. In the next 5 years, high capacity cellular internet coverage (4G and 5G) in the countryside is expected to cover an area corresponding to that which 2G and 3G technologies took 20 years to achieve. The development of the entire agribusiness chain from the IoT and with the advent of 5G can make Brazil even more productive than it is today. The global demand for plant inputs, food and protein will double by 2050 and Brazil is the only large country, with favorable conditions to increase in scale the supply of food, in addition to huge space for productivity gains in different stages of the chain, becoming the largest exporter of agricultural products in this new decade&amp;rdquo;, adds Ricotta.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho is among the largest sugar-energy groups in Brazil, with an approximate crushing capacity of 24 million tons of sugarcane and an average harvest mechanization rate of 100%, a benchmark in the sector. It has four units in operation: Usina S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, in Prad&amp;oacute;polis, in the Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto region (SP); Usina Iracema, in Iracem&amp;aacute;polis, in the region of Limeira (SP); Usina Santa Cruz, located in Am&amp;eacute;rico Brasiliense (SP) and Usina Boa Vista, in Quirin&amp;oacute;polis, 300 kilometers from Goi&amp;acirc;nia (GO).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, Santa Cruz and Iracema mills produce sugar and ethanol, while the Boa Vista mill is dedicated exclusively to the production of ethanol. All of them generate electricity from the burning of sugarcane bagasse, guaranteeing self-sufficiency and selling the surplus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The Company has a differentiated logistics platform for product transportation, due to its high storage capacity and the proximity to important highways and railways, also having its own railway branch, resulting in great operational and logistics agility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;After a comprehensive professionalization process, as of February 2007, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho had its shares traded on the Novo Mercado, the highest corporate governance segment of the S&amp;atilde;o Paulo Stock Exchange (B3), under the ticker SMTO3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ericsson&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Founded in 1876 in Stockholm, Sweden, and present for 95 years in Brazil, Ericsson is a protagonist in the main technological leaps registered in the country and in the world, being a reference in technology, communications, hardware, software and services. It is recognized worldwide as a leader in digital platforms and mobile networks, not only in construction and infrastructure, but in their relevance to society and the economy of the countries in which it operates, with a reputation built on technical competence and its ability to innovation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Ericsson pioneered the implementation of 5G on five continents and today there are more than 60 active commercial operations using Ericsson&amp;#39;s 5G technology in the United States, Germany, Switzerland, the Middle East, Australia, South Korea, China, Brazil, among others&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Ericsson has been operating in Brazil since 1924, but the Swedish company&amp;#39;s first interaction in the country occurred in 1877, when it installed here, at the request of Emperor Dom Pedro II, the first landline. Since then, we have assumed a leading role in the telecommunications sector in the Brazilian market, which is repeated for the network infrastructure sector. We are leaders in 2G, 3G, 4G and we will also be in 5G. We have a high-performance factory installed in S&amp;atilde;o Jos&amp;eacute; dos Campos / SP since 1955, one of the five manufacturing plants that Ericsson maintains in the world and is today the oldest in uninterrupted operation, exporting 40% of the total produced.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The company also maintains a Center of Excellence in R &amp;amp; D &amp;amp; I in Indaiatuba / SP, where more than 450 researchers work. More than 140 patents were developed locally as a result of this work and, making a cut only in the last twenty years, more than R $ 1 billion were invested. Ericsson is ready to take the lead in the advancement of 5G in Latin America. In November last year, the company announced a robust investment of R $ 1 billion in research, development and manufacturing of 5G in Brazil, for the period from 2020 to 2025.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=TWDKhhpildYzavwc+hMxFw==" style="width: 400px; height: 266px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=eBhIGPn9JoW7Ai8vD9vC+Q==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Fri, 18 Sep 2020 11:41:00 GMT</pubDate><title>For the fifth straight year, São Martinho is elected one of Brazil’s most innovative companies</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;FOR THE FIFTH STRAIGHT YEAR, S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO IS ELECTED ONE OF BRAZIL&amp;rsquo;S MOST INNOVATIVE COMPANIES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, September 18 2020 -&lt;/b&gt; For the fifth straight year, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho is one of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s most innovative companies, according to &lt;i&gt;Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico&lt;/i&gt;, based on the survey conducted in partnership with Strategy&amp;amp;, a strategic consultancy of PwC, in the 6&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the &amp;ldquo;Valor Brasil Innovation Awards 2020&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho also figured 4&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; among the Top 5 most innovative companies in the Agribusiness industry. In four recent editions of the awards (2016, 2018, 2019 and 2020), S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has figured among the top five companies in the agriculture sector.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Presented in a ceremony streamed online on September 17, the award recognized S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;rsquo;s management capacity, investment in new solutions and total commitment to innovation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The survey evaluated the practices of 23 sectors of the economy based on their investments in research, development and innovation. The ranking was compiled based on five pillars of the innovation chain: innovation plans, innovation efforts, results obtained, market evaluation and knowledge generation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;According to Fabio Venturelli, CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, garnering the recognition once again reflects and confirms the company&amp;rsquo;s vocation for innovation. &amp;ldquo;It is a great honor to figure, for the fifth straight year, among Brazil&amp;rsquo;s most innovative companies. Investing regularly in innovation and in people development is in S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&amp;rsquo;s corporate DNA. This is how we help the company and its employees to overcome challenges with creativity, while always contributing to new knowledge and solutions for the sugar and energy sector,&amp;rdquo; said Venturelli.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;For more information about the 6&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition of the &amp;ldquo;Valor Brasil Innovation Awards 2020&amp;rdquo;, see the website: &lt;a href="http://www.premioinovacaobrasil.com.br"&gt;www.premioinovacaobrasil.com.br&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=u5zA1YEw4PgiPfSqSyqEAg==" style="width: 555px; height: 290px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=noe7EYXyOZX2el/eUB6mIg==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Fri, 28 Aug 2020 10:23:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Fabio Venturelli elected Agribusiness “Executivo de Valor” for the sixth time</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FABIO VENTURELLI ELECTED AGRIBUSINESS &amp;ldquo;EXECUTIVO DE VALOR&amp;rdquo; FOR THE SIXTH TIME &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, August&amp;nbsp;28&amp;nbsp;2020&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; In the year it reaches its 20&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; edition, the &amp;ldquo;Executivo de Valor&amp;rdquo; Award, instituted by the Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico newspaper, has elected the CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, Fabio Venturelli, as Executive of the Year in the Agribusiness category for the sixth time. The awards ceremony was held on August 27&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; in a virtual ceremony broadcast by Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico on its YouTube channel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Fabio Venturelli had already won the Valor award in 2012, 2013, 2016, 2017, 2018 and now in 2020. The winners were elected by a jury of headhunters from 16 consulting firms, who selected 23 outstanding leaders in 19 different segments of the economy and also given to four leaders in the following categories: successful startups; chairman of the board of directors; youth leadership; digital transformation and social activism.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;Executivo de Valor&amp;rdquo; is one of the premier awards in Brazil&amp;rsquo;s corporate scenario. As highlighted by the awarding entity, to win the title of &amp;ldquo;Executivo de Valor&amp;rdquo; in a scenario of uncertainties and formidable challenges, &amp;ldquo;CEOs of companies must demonstrate the ability to provide what the market requires, the capacity to build high performance teams, take care of the organization&amp;rsquo;s reputation, keep a watchful eye on the management of innovation and encourage digital transformation&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;During the awards ceremony, Fabio Venturelli thanked Valor Econ&amp;ocirc;mico for the recognition during such a challenging year and dedicated the award to his family, the board of directors of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho and the Company&amp;#39;s employees, who have represented Brazil&amp;#39;s agribusiness sector in a responsible and safe manner. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;He also described his vision of the prospects for CEOs and companies in the post-pandemic scenario. &amp;ldquo;The challenges go through three dimensions. Building resilient organizations, because it has been proven that there is no impossible scenario. Seeking to understand the human element, since we will all emerge from this experience transformed. And the third point is innovation. It is increasingly clear the role played by innovation in making companies and people successful in any type of challenge&amp;rdquo;, he said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://files.workr.com.br/ViewImage.aspx?image=2FAKlI/oiwRW8FNUMQHM9w==" style="width: 232px; height: 350px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=ttOgV2jwKJodQ2tTToKZHg==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2020 17:50:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho supports hiring of medical team for HC in Ribeirão Preto </title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO SUPPORTS PROJECT TO HIRE DOCTORS AND NURSES FOR HOSPITAL DAS CL&amp;Iacute;NICAS IN RIBEIR&amp;Atilde;O PRETO &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;i&gt;The company participates in the joint initiative coordinated by the BTG Pactual bank, in partnership with Cosan and Minerva Foods, which led to the donation of R$1.2 million to the hospital in the interior of S&amp;atilde;o Paulo state&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, July&amp;nbsp;15&amp;nbsp;2020&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, one of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s largest sugar and ethanol groups, has joined forces in another solidarity action to combat the covid-19 pandemic in the country. The company supported the project to fund the hiring of 55 doctors and nursing technicians for Hospital das Cl&amp;iacute;nicas at the University of S&amp;atilde;o Paulo at Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto (HCFMRP-USP) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The recruitment of health professionals is receiving assistance from the Foundation for Support to Teaching, Research and Assistance of HCFMRP-USP (FAEPA) and made possible by a donation of R$1.2 million, in partnership with the BTG Pactual bank, Cosan and Minerva Foods. The new team of physicians and nursing technicians will make possible 130 extra shifts per month, or nearly 1,600 work hours.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;We remain vigilant and committed to initiatives to support healthcare professionals across the country and the fight against covid-19. We&amp;rsquo;ve already mobilized part of our alcohol production and partners in the sugar and ethanol sector to contribute with other such measures, and we hope that this team of doctors and nurses brings comfort to those who need it most at Hospital das Cl&amp;iacute;nicas in Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto,&amp;rdquo; said Fabio Venturelli, CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time for solidarity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Since the start of the pandemic in Brazil, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has collaborated with the public and private sector initiatives to prevent and contain the risks of the new coronavirus for the public.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Among the many actions already taken, such as donations of alcohol 70% and medical equipment to healthcare institutions, the Company has produced 150,000 liters of alcohol 70%, which were used to make 15,000 kilos of alcohol gel in partnership with Natura &amp;amp; Co, and sent to the S&amp;atilde;o Paulo State Health Department.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In another joint effort with the Sugarcane Industry Association (Unica), S&amp;atilde;o Martinho contributed to the donation of 1 million liters of alcohol 70% to supply the National Health System (SUS) and Santa Casa Hospitals in 302 municipalities in the state of S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, with support from Coca-Cola FEMSA.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho is one of the largest sugar and ethanol groups in Brazil, with approximate crushing capacity of 24 million tons per crop year and a maximum mechanized harvesting rate of 100%, and a reference in agricultural and industrial management. S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has a unique logistics platform for product distribution, high storage capacity and proximity to key highway and rail systems, and also has its own rail branch. After a comprehensive process to professionalize its management, in February 2007, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho listed its stock on the Novo Mercado, the listing segment of the B3 with the highest corporate governance requirements. For more information, visit: &lt;a href="https://www.saomartinho.com.br/"&gt;www.saomartinho.com.br&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=P7KNFVgH5X4cdmifU5bm1A==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2020 15:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho participates in the donation of 1 million liters of alcohol to Brazil’s public health service</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO PARTICIPATES IN THE DONATION OF 1 MILLION LITERS OF ALCOHOL TO BRAZIL&amp;#39;S&amp;nbsp;PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Action is being coordinated by UNICA, which has already received requests from six states through the health departments for the production of hand sanitizer and 70% alcohol, which are in short supply and are essential at this moment&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, April 1st 2020&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, one of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s largest sugar and ethanol producers, has joined the collective effort to donate 1 million liters of alcohol to produce hand sanitizer and 70% alcohol to be used to contain the coronavirus outbreak. The goal is to help supply the public health centers free of charge.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has been taking all efforts to fight the coronavirus and this coordinated action by the industry through UNICA, the sugarcane industry association, comes at a crucial moment. Our duty as a company is to ensure, above all, the well-being of humanity through our work&amp;rdquo;, says Fabio Venturelli, CEO of S&amp;atilde;o Martinho. In late March, the Company had already announced a partnership with Natura and Avon to process and bottle 70% alcohol for donation to the S&amp;atilde;o Paulo State Health Department.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;In this new phase, as part of the massive campaign coordinated by UNICA involving 572 towns in the state of S&amp;atilde;o Paulo&amp;nbsp;with approximately 44 million inhabitants, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho will contribute to the donation of alcohol to the regions of Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto, Barretos, Franca, S&amp;atilde;o Jos&amp;eacute; do Rio Preto, Araraquara and Campinas. Through the two actions, S&amp;atilde;o Martinho has already donated about 205,000 liters of alcohol.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;UNICA, in which S&amp;atilde;o Martinho is a member, is interacting with state health departments to receive the requests and coordinate withdrawals from producers. This action will be assisted by members of the Brazilian Association for the Transport and Logistics of Hazardous Products (ABTLP), who will transport the cargo in their own vehicles, and the National Fuel and Lubricant Distribution Companies Union (Sindicom), which is donating the diesel that will be used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Overall, six states will receive this donation: S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, Rio de Janeiro, Rio Grande do Sul, Esp&amp;iacute;rito Santo, Paran&amp;aacute; and Santa Catarina. The 70% alcohol to be donated will be produced voluntarily after Brazil&amp;rsquo;s National Health Surveillance Agency (ANVISA) granted an extraordinary temporary authorization on March 19 for its production on an exceptional basis. The product is used for disinfection and is essential for health services.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;The cargo will be transported to locations indicated by the Health Departments of these states, where it will undergo industrial processing to be transformed into gel or for bottling the liquid solution. After that, its distribution to public health centers will be coordinated by the State Health Departments. The entire operation is complying with the hygiene and safety guidelines established by the Ministry of Health and Anvisa.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=hAp8YZT2nBRAFBG6h5wB1g==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Mon, 23 Mar 2020 19:39:00 GMT</pubDate><title>São Martinho anuncia a doação de 150 mil litros de álcool em solução 70% para a Secretaria de Saúde do Estado de São Paulo, em parceria com a Avon e a Natura &amp;Co</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;Atilde;O MARTINHO ANUNCIA A DOA&amp;Ccedil;&amp;Atilde;O DE 150 MIL LITROS DE &amp;Aacute;LCOOL EM SOLU&amp;Ccedil;&amp;Atilde;O 70% PARA A SECRETARIA DE SA&amp;Uacute;DE DO ESTADO DE S&amp;Atilde;O PAULO, EM PARCERIA COM A AVON E A NATURA &amp;amp;CO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;A parceria entre a S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, Avon e Natura &amp;amp;Co visa a produ&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o e doa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de &amp;aacute;lcool l&amp;iacute;quido 70% e &amp;aacute;lcool em gel para combate ao coronav&amp;iacute;rus.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&amp;atilde;o Paulo, 23 de mar&amp;ccedil;o de 2020&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; No intuito de contribuir para a mitiga&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o e combate ao coronavirus, a S&amp;atilde;o Martinho anuncia a doa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de 150 mil litros de &amp;aacute;lcool em solu&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o 70% para a Secretaria de Sa&amp;uacute;de do Estado de S&amp;atilde;o Paulo. A a&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o, que conta com a parceria da Natura &amp;amp;Co Am&amp;eacute;rica Latina, grupo que re&amp;uacute;ne Avon, Natura, The Body Shop e AESOP na regi&amp;atilde;o, doar&amp;aacute; tamb&amp;eacute;m 15 mil quilos de &amp;aacute;lcool em gel, a serem processados e envasados na f&amp;aacute;brica da Avon, localizada em Interlagos, na cidade de S&amp;atilde;o Paulo.&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
O item de higiene, que n&amp;atilde;o faz parte do portf&amp;oacute;lio oficial de produtos de ambas as Companhias, ser&amp;aacute; produzido em parceria e doado em frascos de 750 ml para uso nos postos de sa&amp;uacute;de de todo o Estado de S&amp;atilde;o Paulo. A Avon ficar&amp;aacute; respons&amp;aacute;vel pelo processamento e envase enquanto a S&amp;atilde;o Martinho fornecer&amp;aacute; a mat&amp;eacute;ria prima.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Sobre a S&amp;atilde;o Martinho&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
A S&amp;atilde;o Martinho &amp;eacute; considerada um dos maiores grupos sucroenerg&amp;eacute;ticos do Brasil, com capacidade aproximada de moagem de 24 milh&amp;otilde;es de toneladas de cana-de-a&amp;ccedil;&amp;uacute;car por safra, com &amp;iacute;ndice m&amp;aacute;ximo de mecaniza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de colheita de 100%, sendo refer&amp;ecirc;ncia no setor na gest&amp;atilde;o agr&amp;iacute;cola e industrial. A Companhia possui uma diferenciada plataforma log&amp;iacute;stica para escoamento de produtos, alta capacidade de armazenagem e a proximidade de importantes rodovias e ferrovias, al&amp;eacute;m de possuir um ramal ferrovi&amp;aacute;rio pr&amp;oacute;prio. Ap&amp;oacute;s um abrangente processo de profissionaliza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o, a partir de fevereiro de 2007, a S&amp;atilde;o Martinho listou suas a&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es na B3, pelo Novo Mercado, segmento mais elevado de governan&amp;ccedil;a corporativa.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sobre a Natura &amp;amp;Co&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Resultado da combina&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o entre Avon, Natura, Aesop e The Body Shop, Natura &amp;amp;Co consolida a cria&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de um grupo de cosm&amp;eacute;ticos global, multicanal e multimarcas, movido por prop&amp;oacute;sitos. Em 2019, a Natura &amp;amp;Co registrou receita l&amp;iacute;quida de R$ 14,4 bilh&amp;otilde;es. As quatro empresas do grupo est&amp;atilde;o empenhadas em gerar impactos econ&amp;ocirc;micos, sociais e ambientais positivos. Avon Cosm&amp;eacute;ticos foi fundada em 1886 por David McConnell e empodera mulheres com inspira&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o e independ&amp;ecirc;ncia financeira. Fundada em 1969 por Luiz Seabra, a Natura &amp;eacute; uma multinacional brasileira de higiene e cosm&amp;eacute;tica, l&amp;iacute;der no setor de venda direta no Brasil. Fundada em 1976 em Brighton, na Inglaterra, por Anita Roddick, a The Body Shop &amp;eacute; uma marca de beleza global que procura fazer diferen&amp;ccedil;a no mundo. Criada em 1987, a marca australiana Aesop tem a miss&amp;atilde;o de oferecer um portf&amp;oacute;lio de produtos superlativos para a pele, cabelo e corpo. Saiba mais em &lt;a href="http://www.naturaeco.com" target="_blank"&gt;www.naturaeco.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sobre a Avon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A Avon, a empresa voltada para as mulheres, comercializa seus produtos em aproximadamente 50 pa&amp;iacute;ses por meio de cerca de 6 milh&amp;otilde;es de revendedores aut&amp;ocirc;nomos. O portf&amp;oacute;lio de produtos da Avon inclui itens de beleza de alta tecnologia e apresenta marcas de qualidade mundialmente reconhecidas como Avon True, Mark, Color Trend, Mark, Renew, Advance Techniques, Avon Care e Avon Naturals. Al&amp;eacute;m disso, o portf&amp;oacute;lio de Avon inclui produtos de vestu&amp;aacute;rio como a linha de lingerie Avon Signature e voltados para a casa como Innovaware. A empresa &amp;eacute; pioneira em venda direta de cosm&amp;eacute;ticos no Brasil, onde est&amp;aacute; desde 1958. Atualmente, o pa&amp;iacute;s conta com a maior for&amp;ccedil;a de vendas da Avon &amp;ndash; mais de um milh&amp;otilde;es de revendedoras - e &amp;eacute; tamb&amp;eacute;m a maior opera&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o da companhia no mundo. Para obter mais informa&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es sobre a Avon no mundo, visite o site: &lt;a href="http://www.avoncompany.com" target="_blank"&gt;www.avoncompany.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=2kf53YNw7TkSm3s3wpc0YA==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Tue, 03 Dec 2019 15:59:00 GMT</pubDate><title>11th Edition of the SM Race gathered the record of 2.1 thousand participants (portuguese only)</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;11&amp;ordf; Edi&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o da Corrida SM reuniu o recorde de 2,1 mil participantes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Provas de 5 e 10 km s&amp;atilde;o realizadas pela Usina S&amp;atilde;o Martinho em trilhas de terra e grama, passando por reservas naturais e canaviais da usina, em Prad&amp;oacute;polis - SP&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A 11&amp;ordf; Edi&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o da Corrida SM, realizada no dia 01 de dezembro, na Usina S&amp;atilde;o Martinho, em Prad&amp;oacute;polis &amp;ndash; SP, registrou um recorde de 2,1 mil participantes. Atletas profissionais e amadores, al&amp;eacute;m de colaboradores da Companhia, participaram da tradicional corrida realizada pela empresa em percursos que contam com trilhas de terra e grama, passando por matas, reservas verdes e canaviais da usina.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Ao longo dos anos, a prova vem aumentando o n&amp;uacute;mero de participantes e conquistando espa&amp;ccedil;o na agenda das grandes corridas promovidas no interior do Estado de S&amp;atilde;o Paulo. O evento esportivo atrai atletas de elite que se preparam para a S&amp;atilde;o Silvestre e outras provas e muitos adeptos da corrida.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Em 11 anos de organiza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o, a Corrida SM saltou de 200 participantes em sua primeira edi&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o para 2,1 mil corredores. S&amp;atilde;o atletas amadores, profissionais e colaboradores da S&amp;atilde;o Martinho que disputam provas de 5 e 10 km. O evento tamb&amp;eacute;m conta com a participa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de crian&amp;ccedil;as entre 8 e 14 anos, que vivenciam a experi&amp;ecirc;ncia de correr pequenas dist&amp;acirc;ncias e o clima de uma prova.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Na disputa dos 10 km Masculino, o vencedor foi Glenison Gilbert de Carvalho, com o tempo de 32:59 min. No feminino, a atleta Amanda Aparecida de Oliveira ganhou com o tempo de 39:27 min. No percurso de 5 km, os vencedores foram Alexandre Ribeiro Pastorello, com o tempo de 16:08 min, no masculino, e Val&amp;eacute;ria Sanches Pietro, com o tempo de 19:34 min, no feminino, ganhadora da prova em 2018. Os cinco primeiros em cada categoria tamb&amp;eacute;m receberam pr&amp;ecirc;mios em dinheiro.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Os colaboradores da S&amp;atilde;o Martinho disputaram categorias internas no masculino e feminino nas dist&amp;acirc;ncias de 5 e 10 km. Na prova de 10 km, foram premiados com dinheiro os cinco primeiros colocados em cada categoria. Os classificados entre 6&amp;ordm; e 10&amp;ordm; lugar receberam trof&amp;eacute;us. Na prova de 5 km, os cinco primeiros em cada categoria receberam premia&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o em dinheiro. Confira os resultados dos colaboradores da S&amp;atilde;o Martinho:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Masculino 10 km &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;1&amp;ordm;- Diones Renis Hor&amp;aacute;cio Medeiros da Silva (36:04); 2&amp;ordm;- Jos&amp;eacute; Roberto Pedrozo (38:23); 3&amp;ordm;- Nelicio Santos de Souza (39:16); 4&amp;ordm;- Reginaldo Eduardo Manoel (40:13); e 5&amp;ordm;- A&amp;eacute;cio Gomes Ferreira (42:55).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feminino 10 km&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp;1&amp;ordm;- Marli Borges Silva (54:20); 2&amp;ordm;- Juliana Queiroz Beraldo Culotti (01:00:15); 3&amp;ordm;- Mariane Sampaio de Aguiar Magalh&amp;atilde;es (01:04:22); 4&amp;ordm;- Lorane Dolfi (01:06:03); e Ana Fl&amp;aacute;via Fedato Zarro (01:06:24).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Masculino 5 km&lt;/strong&gt; - 1&amp;ordm;- Daniel Barros Marques (19:35); 2&amp;ordm;- Gilson Carvalho Cordeiro (19:42); 3&amp;ordm;- Mathias Machado Valente (19:55); 4&amp;ordm;- Luciano Bispo dos Santos (20:06); e 5&amp;ordm;- Roni Cesar Medeiros da Silva (20:16).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feminino 5 km&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp;1&amp;ordm;- Maria Aparecida Ferreira (26:53); 2&amp;ordm;- Ionice de Ara&amp;uacute;jo (29:59); 3&amp;ordm;- Juliana Anacleto (31:38); 4&amp;ordm;- Gleisismara Ferreira de Almeida(36:11); e 5&amp;ordm;- Thais Terzner Barbosa (36:32).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A 10&amp;ordf; Edi&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o da Corrida SM foi promovida com o apoio da City Vida Academia e Unimed Jaboticabal, e contou com organiza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o da Paulinho Sports. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A S&amp;atilde;o Martinho promove h&amp;aacute; 11 anos a corrida com objetivo de estimular a pr&amp;aacute;tica de exerc&amp;iacute;cios e uma vida mais saud&amp;aacute;vel entre seus colaboradores e a comunidade. A Companhia parabeniza a todos os participantes, atletas profissionais e amadores, colaboradores da empresa que se dedicam ao esporte.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Confira o resultado completo da corrida no site: &lt;a href="http://paulinhosports.com.br/resultados" target="_blank"&gt;http://paulinhosports.com.br/resultados&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description><link>https://www.saomartinho.com.br/show.aspx?idMateria=OKCxUT/B4dyQ0fv5SVxqkQ==&amp;linguagem=en</link></item><item><pubDate>Tue, 03 Dec 2019 15:53:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Iracema mill year-end meeting gathers community in Iracemápolis-SP (portuguese only)</title><description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Encontro de fim de ano da Usina Iracema re&amp;uacute;ne comunidade em Iracem&amp;aacute;polis-SP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tradicional evento de confraterniza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o foi realizado no dia 28 de novembro no Teatro Virg&amp;iacute;nio Ometto e contou com apresenta&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es da Orquestra Sinf&amp;ocirc;nica de Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto e do Coro Infantojuvenil da orquestra&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;M&amp;uacute;sica, boas not&amp;iacute;cias, importantes conquistas e confraterniza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o embalaram o tradicional encontro de fim de ano promovido pela Usina Iracema no dia 28 de novembro, em Iracem&amp;aacute;polis-SP. O evento reuniu representantes da comunidade, imprensa e convidados especiais da empresa.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A noite teve in&amp;iacute;cio com um coquetel receptivo realizado na sede da Aril &amp;ndash; Associa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de Reabilita&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Infantil Limeirense, e seguiu com a programa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o musical apresentada no Teatro Virg&amp;iacute;nio Ometto.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;O presidente da S&amp;atilde;o Martinho Fabio Venturelli deu as boas-vindas aos convidados, destacando que o evento &amp;eacute; o grande momento do ano para interagir de forma especial com a comunidade de Iracem&amp;aacute;polis, local onde toda a hist&amp;oacute;ria da Companhia se iniciou. Venturelli ainda ressaltou as conquistas e bons resultados da empresa em 2019.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&amp;ldquo;Somos pelo terceiro ano consecutivo eleita pela pesquisa Voc&amp;ecirc; S/A a melhor empresa do agroneg&amp;oacute;cio para se trabalhar. Estamos entre as poucas empresas brasileiras a conquistar grau de investimento. E a Iracema tamb&amp;eacute;m tem muito o que celebrar, a unidade passou a cogerar energia e &amp;eacute; parte fundamental de uma Companhia que integra a inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o com o valor do elemento humano para alcan&amp;ccedil;ar suas conquistas&amp;rdquo;, falou F&amp;aacute;bio Venturelli, que ainda desejou &amp;oacute;timas festas para todos.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;M&amp;uacute;sica&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align: justify;"&gt;A abertura das apresenta&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es musicais ficou por conta do Coro Infantojuvenil da Orquestra Sinf&amp;ocirc;nica de Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto &amp;ndash; OSRP. O projeto de educa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o musical j&amp;aacute; formou cerca de 700 jovens. Na sequ&amp;ecirc;ncia, teve in&amp;iacute;cio o espet&amp;aacute;culo principal da noite com a Orquestra Sinf&amp;ocirc;nica de Ribeir&amp;atilde;o Preto, composta por 37 m&amp;uacute;sicos e regida pelo maestro Reginaldo Nascimento. No repert&amp;oacute;rio, cl&amp;aacute;ssicos do cinema como os temas de Star Wars, Cinema Paradiso, Cantando na Chuva, Era uma Vez no Oeste, entre outros, apresentados para um p&amp;uacute;blico de mais de 250 pessoas, que lotou o teatro Virg&amp;iacute;nio Ometto.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

